{"title": "The post-transcriptional steps of eukaryotic ribosome biogenesis", "url": "https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s00018-008-8027-0", "author": "AK Henras and J Soudet and M Gerus and S Lebaron\u2026", "abstract": "One of the most important tasks of any cell is to synthesize ribosomes. In eukaryotes, this process occurs sequentially in the nucleolus, the nucleoplasm and the cytoplasm. It involves the transcription and processing of pre-ribosomal RNAs, their proper folding and assembly \u2026"}